e loop statement\', \'The do...while loop statement\', \'The foreach loop statement\', \'The break statement\', \'The continue statement\', \'Useful Video Courses\']','[\'Syntax\', \'Example\', \'Syntax\', \'Example\', \'Syntax\', \'Example\', \'Syntax\', \'Example\', \'Example\', \'Example\']','[\'https://www.tutorialspoint.com/php/php_decision_making.htm\', \'https://www.tutorialspoint.com/php/php_arrays.htm\', \'http://tpcg.io/n7ropq\', \'http://tpcg.io/tsLS0l\', \'http://tpcg.io/glAjbK\', \'http://tpcg.io/FA1hw2\', \'http://tpcg.io/dQeDDw\', \'http://tpcg.io/Maa3wb\', \'https://www.tutorialspoint.com/php_online_training/index.asp\', \'https://www.tutorialspoint.com/php_online_training/index.asp\', \'https://www.tutorialspoint.com/profile/malhar_lathkar\', \'https://www.tutorialspoint.com/php_online_training/index.asp\', \'https://www.tutorialspoint.com/become_php_facebook_developer_password_less_authentication/index.asp\', \'https://www.tutorialspoint.com/become_php_facebook_developer_password_less_authentication/index.asp\', \'https://www.tutorialspoint.com/profile/syed_raza\', \'https://www.tutorialspoint.com/become_php_facebook_developer_password_less_authentication/index.asp\', \'https://www.tutorialspoint.com/ultimate_php_and_mysql_web_development_course_and_oop_coding/index.asp\', \'https://www.tutorialspoint.com/ultimate_php_and_mysql_web_development_course_and_oop_coding/index.asp\', \'https://www.tutorialspoint.com/profile/frahaan_hussain\', \'https://www.tutorialspoint.com/ultimate_php_and_mysql_web_development_course_and_oop_coding/index.asp\', \'https://www.tutorialspoint.com/learn_php_from_scratch/index.asp\', \'https://www.tutorialspoint.com/learn_php_from_scratch/index.asp\', \'https://www.tutorialspoint.com/profile/nivedita_jain\', \'https://www.tutorialspoint.com/learn_php_from_scratch/index.asp\', \'https://www.tutorialspoint.com/e_commerce_website_development_in_php_with_pdo/index.asp\', \'https://www.tutorialspoint.com/e_commerce_website_development_in_php_with_pdo/index.asp\', \'https://www.tutorialspoint.com/profile/azaz_patel\', \'https://www.tutorialspoint.com/e_commerce_website_development_in_php_with_pdo/index.asp\', \'https://www.tutorialspoint.com/php_in_telugu/index.asp\', \'https://www.tutorialspoint.com/php_in_telugu/index.asp\', \'https://www.tutorialspoint.com/profile/vijay_kumar_parvatha_reddy\', \'https://www.tutorialspoint.com/php_in_telugu/index.asp\', \'https://www.tutorialspoint.com/php/php_decision_making.htm\', \'https://www.tutorialspoint.comjavascript:printPage();\', \'https://www.tutorialspoint.com/php/php_arrays.htm\']','[\'https://www.tutorialspoint.com/php/images/php_for_loop.jpg\', \'https://www.tutorialspoint.com/php/images/php_while_loop.jpg\', \'https://www.tutorialspoint.com/php/images/cpp_break_statement.jpg\', \'https://www.tutorialspoint.com/php/images/cpp_continue_statement.jpg\', \'https://d3mxt5v3yxgcsr.cloudfront.net/courses/1981/course_1981_image.png\', \'https://d3mxt5v3yxgcsr.cloudfront.net/courses/2564/course_2564_image.jpg\', \'https://d3mxt5v3yxgcsr.cloudfront.net/courses/2644/course_2644_image.png\', \'https://d3mxt5v3yxgcsr.cloudfront.net/courses/2668/course_2668_image.png\', \'https://d3mxt5v3yxgcsr.cloudfront.net/courses/2694/course_2694_image.png\', \'https://d3mxt5v3yxgcsr.cloudfront.net/courses/2848/course_2848_image.jpg\']','[\'for âˆ’ loops through a block of code a specified number of times.\', \'foreach âˆ’ loops through a block of code for each element in an array.\', \'This will produce the following result âˆ’\', \'This will produce the following result âˆ’\', \'This will produce the following result âˆ’\', \'Try out following example to list out the values of an array.\', \'This will produce the following result âˆ’\', \'The PHP break keyword is used to terminate the execution of a loop prematurely.\', \'This will produce the following result âˆ’\', \'This will produce the following result âˆ’\']','[\'while âˆ’ loops through a block of code if and as long as a specified condition is true.\', \'do...while âˆ’ loops through a block of code once, and then repeats the loop as long as a special condition is true.\', \'We will discuss about continue and break keywords used to control the loops execution.\', \'The for statement is used when you know how many times you want to execute a statement or a block of statements.\', \'The following example makes five iterations and changes the assigned value of two variables on each pass of the loop âˆ’\', \'The while statement will execute a block of code if and as long as a test expression is true.\', \'In the following example condition test becomes true when the counter value reaches 3 and loop terminates.\', \'The PHP continue keyword is used to halt the current iteration of a loop but it does not terminate the loop.\']','[\'Loops in PHP are used to execute the same block of code a specified number of times. PHP supports following four loop types.\', \'The initializer is used to set the start value for the counter of the number of loop iterations. A variable may be declared here for this purpose and it is traditional to name it $i.\', \'If the test expression is true then the code block will be executed. After the code has executed the test expression will again be evaluated and the loop will continue until the test expression is found to be false.\', \'This example decrements a variable value on each iteration of the loop and the counter increments until it reaches 10 when the evaluation is false and the loop ends.\', \'The do...while statement will execute a block of code at least once - it then will repeat the loop as long as a condition is true.\', \'The following example will increment the value of i at least once, and it will continue incrementing the variable i as long as it has a value of less than 10 âˆ’\', \'The foreach statement is used to loop through arrays. For each pass the value of the current array element is assigned to $value and the array pointer is moved by one and in the next pass next element will be processed.\', \'The break statement is situated inside the statement block. It gives you full control and whenever you want to exit from the loop you can come out. After coming out of a loop immediate statement to the loop will be executed.\', \'Just like the break statement the continue statement is situated inside the statement block containing the code that the loop executes, preceded by a conditional test. For the pass encountering continue statement, rest of the loop code is skipped and next pass starts.\', \'In the following example loop prints the value of array but for which condition becomes true it just skip the code and next value is printed.\']','[\'\nfor (initialization; condition; increment){\n   code to be executed;\n}\n\', \'\n<html>\n   <body>\n      \n      <?php\n         $a = 0;\n         $b = 0;\n         \n         for( $i = 0; $i<5; $i++ ) {\n            $a += 10;\n            $b += 5;\n         }\n         \n         echo (\"At the end of the loop a = $a and b = $b\" );\n      ?>\n   \n   </body>\n</html>\n\', \'\nAt the end of the loop a = 50 and b = 25\n\', \'\nwhile (condition) {\n   code to be executed;\n}\n\', \'\n<html>\n   <body>\n   \n      <?php\n         $i = 0;\n         $num = 50;\n         \n         while( $i < 10) {\n            $num--;\n            $i++;\n         }\n         \n         echo (\"Loop stopped at i = $i and num = $num\" );\n      ?>\n      \n   </body>\n</html>\n\', \'\nLoop stopped at i = 10 and num = 40 \n\', \'\ndo {\n   code to be executed;\n}\nwhile (condition);\n\', \'\n<html>\n   <body>\n   \n      <?php\n         $i = 0;\n         $num = 0;\n         \n         do {\n            $i++;\n         }\n         \n         while( $i < 10 );\n         echo (\"Loop stopped at i = $i\" );\n      ?>\n      \n   </body>\n</html>\n\', \'\nLoop stopped at i = 10\n\', \'\nforeach (array as value) {\n   code to be executed;\n}\n\', \'\n<html>\n   <body>\n   \n      <?php\n         $array = array( 1, 2, 3, 4, 5);\n         \n         foreach( $array as $value ) {\n            echo \"Value is $value <br />\";\n         }\n      ?>\n      \n   </body>\n</html>\n\', \'\nValue is 1\nValue is 2\nValue is 3\nValue is 4\nValue is 5\n\', \'\n<html>\n   <body>\n   \n      <?php\n         $i = 0;\n         \n         while( $i < 10) {\n            $i++;\n            if( $i == 3 )break;\n         }\n         echo (\"Loop stopped at i = $i\" );\n      ?>\n   \n   </body>\n</html>\n\', \'\nLoop stopped at i = 3\n\', \'\n<html>\n   <body>\n   \n      <?php\n         $array = array( 1, 2, 3, 4, 5);\n         \n         foreach( $array as $value ) {\n            if( $value == 3 )continue;\n            echo \"Value is $value <br />\";\n         }\n      ?>\n   \n   </body>\n</html>\n\', \'\nValue is 1\nValue is 2\nValue is 4\nValue is 5\n\']','[\'\nfor (initialization; condition; increment){\n   code to be executed;\n}\n\', \'\nAt the end of the loop a = 50 and b = 25\n\', \'\nwhile (condition) {\n   code to be executed;\n}\n\', \'\nLoop stopped at i = 10 and num = 40 \n\', \'\ndo {\n   code to be executed;\n}\nwhile (condition);\n\', \'\nLoop stopped at i = 10\n\', \'\nforeach (array as value) {\n   code to be executed;\n}\n\', \'\nValue is 1\nValue is 2\nValue is 3\nValue is 4\nValue is 5\n\', \'\nLoop stopped at i = 3\n\', \'\nValue is 1\nValue is 2\nValue is 4\nValue is 5\n\']','[]','[\'for âˆ’ loops through a block of code a specified number of times.|||while âˆ’ loops through a block of code if and as long as a specified condition is true.|||do...while âˆ’ loops through a block of code once, and then repeats the loop as long as a special condition is true.|||foreach âˆ’ loops through a block of code for each element in an array.|||\']'),(9,'[\'PHP - Arrays\']','[\'Numeric Array\', \'Associative Arrays\', \'Multidimensional Arrays\', \'Useful Video Courses\']','[\'Example\', \'Example\', \'Example\']','[\'https://www.tutorialspoint.com